src.nn_library.nn_architectures.architecture_A(input_shape, num_of_classes, layer_activation_function)

Function that initializes Shallow MLP (Multilayer perceptron) model using A architecture. Multidimensional input (image in numpy array type) is converted to one dimension. Only two hidden dense layers.

Parameters

  • input_shape – input shape for the model

  • num_of_classes – number of output classes for the model

  • layer_activation_function – str name of nn layer activation function

Returns

Shallow MLP model

src.nn_library.nn_architectures.architecture_B(input_shape, num_of_classes, layer_activation_function)

Function that initializes Deep MLP (Multilayer perceptron) model using B architecture. Multidimensional input (image in numpy array type) is converted to one dimension. Only hidden dense layers.

Parameters

  • input_shape – input shape for the model

  • num_of_classes – number of output classes for the model

  • layer_activation_function – str name of nn layer activation function

Returns

Deep MLP model

src.nn_library.nn_architectures.architecture_C(input_shape, num_of_classes, layer_activation_function)

Function that initializes Shallow CNN (Convolutional Neural Network) model using C architecture.

Parameters

  • input_shape – input shape for the model

  • num_of_classes – number of output classes for the model

  • layer_activation_function – str name of nn layer activation function

Returns

Shallow CNN model

src.nn_library.nn_architectures.architecture_D(input_shape, num_of_classes, layer_activation_function)

Function that initializes Deep CNN (Convolutional Neural Network) model using D architecture.

Parameters

  • input_shape – input shape for the model

  • num_of_classes – number of output classes for the model

  • layer_activation_function – str name of layer activation function to be used

Returns

Deep CNN model
